    • Method Detail

      • setHistory

        public MigrateTypes.MigrateSpec.Builder setHistory(HistoryMigrationSpec history)
        Determines how vCenter history will be migrated during the migration process. vCenter history consists of:
        • Statistics
        • Events
        • Tasks
        By default only core data will be migrated. Use this spec to define which part of vCenter history data will be migrated and when. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0. If null, only core database content will be migrated.
        Parameters:
        history - New value for the property.

      • setVcsaEmbedded

        public MigrateTypes.MigrateSpec.Builder setVcsaEmbedded(MigrateTypes.VcsaEmbeddedSpec vcsaEmbedded)
        Information specific to an embedded vCenter Server. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0. Only required if the vCenter Server that is going to be migrated is an embedded vCenter Server.
        Parameters:
        vcsaEmbedded - New value for the property.

      • setPsc

        public MigrateTypes.MigrateSpec.Builder setPsc(MigrateTypes.PscSpec psc)
        Information specific to a Platform Services Controller. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0. Only required if the vCenter Server that is going to be migrated is a Platform Services Controller.
        Parameters:
        psc - New value for the property.

      • setActiveDirectory

        public MigrateTypes.MigrateSpec.Builder setActiveDirectory(ActiveDirectorySpec activeDirectory)
        Information specific to the Active Directory server to which the source windows vCenter Server is joined. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0. If null, existing appliance will not be joined to an Active Directory.
        Parameters:
        activeDirectory - New value for the property.

      • setAutoAnswer

        public MigrateTypes.MigrateSpec.Builder setAutoAnswer(java.lang.Boolean autoAnswer)
        Use the default option for any questions that may come up during appliance configuration. This property was added in vSphere API 7.0.0.0. If null, will default to false.
        Parameters:
        autoAnswer - New value for the property.
